<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>For example to get the boot time, I run </p> <pre><code> who -b </code></pre> <p>Which comes back with </p> <pre><code> system boot Apr 21 09:41 </code></pre> <p>I want it to come back in the iso8601 format. </p> <p>I see <em>old</em> references suggesting we use the Danish locale which is <em>weird</em> and likely to produce <em>weird</em> effects elsewhere. </p> <p>I want to use my current locale <em>except</em> show the date in the ISO8601 format.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/buzzwallard"> /u/buzzwallard </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/131epm1/set_global_date_format_to_iso8601/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/131epm1/set_global_date_format_to_iso8601/">[comments]</a></span>